ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
AASPIRE Participant Type / Version Administered
Notes: 1= Direct Report (DR); 2= Direct Report - Supported (DR-S); 3= Caregiver Report (CR)

ElementDescription: On how many days (Direct Report: did / Caregiver Report: do you think) the following problems bother (you/them) over the last two weeks? Feeling nervous, anxious or on edge
Notes: 0= Rarely or not at all; 1= Several days; 2= Half or more than half of the days; 3= Almost every day

ElementDescription: On how many days (Direct Report: did / Caregiver Report: do you think) the following problems bother (you/them) over the last two weeks? Not being able to stop or control worrying
Notes: 0= Rarely or not at all; 1= Several days; 2= Half or more than half of the days; 3= Almost every day

ElementDescription: On how many days (Direct Report: did / Caregiver Report: do you think) the following problems bother (you/them) over the last two weeks? Worrying too much about many different things
Notes: 0= Rarely or not at all; 1= Several days; 2= Half or more than half of the days; 3= Almost every day

ElementDescription: On how many days (Direct Report: did / Caregiver Report: do you think) the following problems bother (you/them) over the last two weeks? Trouble relaxing
Notes: 0= Rarely or not at all; 1= Several days; 2= Half or more than half of the days; 3= Almost every day

ElementDescription: On how many days (Direct Report: did / Caregiver Report: do you think) the following problems bother (you/them) over the last two weeks? Being unable to sit still because (you/they) feel restless
Notes: 0= Rarely or not at all; 1= Several days; 2= Half or more than half of the days; 3= Almost every day

ElementDescription: On how many days (Direct Report: did / Caregiver Report: do you think) the following problems bother (you/them) over the last two weeks? Becoming easily annoyed or angry
Notes: 0= Rarely or not at all; 1= Several days; 2= Half or more than half of the days; 3= Almost every day

ElementDescription: On how many days (Direct Report: did / Caregiver Report: do you think) the following problems bother (you/them) over the last two weeks? Feeling afraid as if something awful might happen
Notes: 0= Rarely or not at all; 1= Several days; 2= Half or more than half of the days; 3= Almost every day

ElementDescription: How hard (Direct Report: have / Caregiver Report: do you think) these things made it for (you/them) to live (your/their) life? For example, have these things made it harder for (you/them) to do (your/their) work, take care of things at home, or get along with other people?
Notes: 0= Not hard at all; 1= Somewhat hard; 2= Very hard; 3= Extremely hard

ElementDescription: Generalized Anxiety - Overall, in the last six months, did the things this survey asked about...
Notes: 1= Get worse; 2= Stay about the same; 3= Get better

ElementDescription: Miscellaneous comments on study, interview, methodology relevant to this form data
Generalized Anxiety Scale - Sum
Notes: Higher numbers indicate levels of anxiety symptoms. Sum of (gad_nervous, gad_worry_ctrl, gad_worry_many, gad_relaxing, gad_restless, gad_angry, gad_afraid)

ElementDescription: Generalized Anxiety Scale - Average
Notes: Higher numbers indicate levels of anxiety symptoms. Mean of non-missing responses from (gad_nervous, gad_worry_ctrl, gad_worry_many, gad_relaxing, gad_restless, gad_angry, gad_afraid)
